5: Whoooa, check it out. Shibuya's lit.
9:
Nyahaha, look at the clothes and
the buildings—everything's different!
This is awesome!
13:
On the other hand, the locals would
probably be shocked to see you—or
any bionic, for that matter.
16:
But more importantly... Should you
really be here, Tink? I thought you
were still working for 3MM Security.
20:
My whole team took off for the
holiday season, so it's all good! 
Even freelancers need a vacay!
23:
Besides, I've always wanted to visit
Shibuya. I still can't believe the cities
got mashed together. It's wild.
26:
Heh, right... That's one way of putting
it.
31:
Anyway, I'm just glad that
everyone's safe and sound.
35:
Yeah, but the city DID get pretty
damaged. Lots of injuries too, so we
need to do whatever I can to help.
50: I almost... had a heart attack...
52:
Monsters... in Shibuya? But how? 
Did they travel all the way here from 
the Kaleidoscope?
55:
They're c-coming from
underground... Over there, near the
Shibuya River!
59:
Holy moly! That IS the Kaleidoscope!
How'd it get here?!
65:
Unless... it appeared during the
merge.
68:
The same thing happened with
Hakunroh. The tremors just got
worse and worse. The abyss began
to spread, and—
72:
So the same pattern's repeating
itself, huh? Isn't there some way to
magically poof things back to how
they were?
76:
Hmm... It's not that simple. But
before we worry about that, 
we have to do something about 
these monsters!
89:
Heya, Auntie! 
Mind if I turn it up a notch?
92:
Just don't go overboard and destroy
any buildings, now! We can't have
another insurance debacle like back
in Qualia City.
94:
Yes, but results come first, don't
they? As long as we get the job
done, I'm sure Zekhel expects a bit of
damage here and there.
95:
Oho... Blow 'em to smithereens,
Chief. 
Call it a New Year's fireworks show!
105:
Those baddies weren't anything for
the Special Equipment Defense
Force SHIBUYA Branch!
110:
Worry not, folks! We've got your
backs no matter how many
monsters rear their ugly mugs.
Pleasure doin' business with ya!
114:
And a very special Happy New Year
to you two!
117:
How do you like my kimono? To die
for, right? Since I'm in Shibuya, 
I thought, "Hey! Do as the Shibuyans
do!"
120:
Happy New Year, Tink! What a lovely
kimono.
123:
Wow, you really went all out, huh?
You look great. But wait... back up a
second. What were you saying
about a "Shibuya branch"?
128:
It's just for the holidays! We
established it to take care of those
monsters coming from the
underground.
131:
Ah, but we're all good and legal! We
got proper authorization from Mr.
Takamori and Zekhel. Gramps made
sure of it!
136: Man, you really do your homework!
139:
Nyahaha, and the best is yet to
come!
145:
TA-DAAA! Welcome to the Shibuya
branch of the Special Equipment
Defense Force!
149:
Good work out there, Chief. I got you
that new ice cream while you were
out!
153:
Huh? What are you guys doing
here? I thought this was Tink's
branch?
156:
She said we could stop by the office
whenever we wanted, so here we
are!
160:
Isn't it great? I had the place built
and decorated just like the locals
would!
163:
Now I can see the sights AND take
care of the city's monster problem!
Two bots, one laser!
168:
Well, that's a big help and all, but...
I'm the one with a responsibility to
Shibuya. I can't just ask you to take
care of everything.
171:
What's wrong with getting a little
help from your friends?
177:
Hehe, now I'm starting to sound like
someone...
181:
Yeah... You're right. We're in this
together. Thanks a lot, Tink!
185:
No problemo, Alk! Now try that
tangerine in front of you—you've
earned yourself a treat!
189:
Mmm, somehow fruit tastes even
better under a warm kotatsu...
194:
It's the life, ain't it? Oh, but you gotta
come check this thing out!
200:
Whoa, an old-school game system!
It looks like something my dad
would've played. It even has
cartridges and everything!
205:
Nyaha! Mr. Takamori refurbished it
for us to celebrate our branch
opening. It's a blast and a half!
211:
Mia helped us find it. Check it out!
We've even got games from back
when we were kids!
218:
Thanks, you guys. It means a lot that
you're here to help out the branch.
221:
And... I'm reeeally sorry for making
you work through your winter break.
224:
Don't tell me you're worryin' about
little ol' us!
227:
I mean, you only get a teeny bit of
time off... then I like, just decided this
for everyone. Plus, I can't just boss
Alk and the others around.
230:
We all decided to come. It was our
choice, so don't you fret one bit. 
Just do what makes you happy.
239: Tink, do you want to play with us?
244:
Absolutely! Game on! And just so
you know, I'm not going easy on you!
